reviewText:
I wish there was a maybe on the recommend. I guess, I'd recommend if it were on sale and/or you need a Spider-Man fix. The game isn't based off the movie per say, there's more characters, but the basis to all Spider-Man stories are the same.... I'll avenge you Uncle Ben.... We get it... Back to the point. This game is fun at times and painstakingly annoying at others.

I'll start with the bad;
1) The controls are incredibly touchy for lack of a better term. And Swinging around is more of a chore than enjoyable. Like swinging from monkey bars as a kid.... It's not a fluid as it could/should be.
2) While swinging around there are events going on all around you. You can either help a person or the police out, or just swing on by... HOWEVER, you have this fancy hero/menace bar that changes pending on what you do... So if you're no where near an event" and/or you don't get there in time you become a menace for some unknown reason. I don't know why you'd be blamed for something that you weren't around for...

The good;
Graphics aren't too bad. I wish I could pan around more to get some screen shots with Spider-Man in it. (Don't ask

